<LanguageData>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.0>questDescription(asker_factionLeader==True)-&gt;[asker_nameDef], [asker_faction_leaderTitle] of [asker_faction_name], has informed us of the location of a sealed entrance to one of the [ancientSilos] left behind during Operation: Deadlife, a planet-spanning initiative launched by a [longDeadGovernment] in preparation for global catastrophe.\n\nThese silos were designed to remain sealed for generations, [intention]. Inside, it's believed they contain [containedReward]. The deeper chambers are rumored to hold equipment and supplies capable of restarting civilization itself.\n\n[threat]. [importantLight]. Without the light, you’ll be navigating blind and vulnerable to attack.\n\n[commandMap]. Studying these might reveal the locations of other silos, and more importantly, bring us closer to discovering the Command Headquarters, the nerve center of Operation: Deadlife, where the truth behind this apocalyptic plan may still lie buried.\n\n[questObjective].</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.0>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.1>questDescription(askerIsNull==True)-&gt;The ancient battle maps have revealed to us the location of a sealed entrance to one of the [ancientSilos] left behind during Operation: Deadlife, a planet-spanning initiative launched by a [longDeadGovernment] in preparation for global catastrophe.\n\nThese silos were designed to remain sealed for generations, [intention]. Inside, it's believed they contain [containedReward]. The deeper chambers are rumored to hold equipment and supplies capable of restarting civilization itself.\n\n[threat]. [importantLight]. Without the light, you’ll be navigating blind and vulnerable to attack.\n\n[commandMap]. Studying these might reveal the locations of other silos, and more importantly, bring us closer to discovering the Command Headquarters, the nerve center of Operation: Deadlife, where the truth behind this apocalyptic plan may still lie buried.\n\n[questObjective].</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.1>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.10>ancientSilos-&gt;deadlife supply silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.10>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.11>longDeadGovernment-&gt;long-dead government</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.11>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.12>longDeadGovernment-&gt;ancient planetary alliance</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.12>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.13>longDeadGovernment-&gt;collapsed technocratic regime</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.13>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.14>longDeadGovernment-&gt;extinct militarized government</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.14>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.15>longDeadGovernment-&gt;forgotten emergency council</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.15>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.16>longDeadGovernment-&gt;defunct crisis-state authority</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.16>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.17>longDeadGovernment-&gt;long-vanished defense network</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.17>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.18>longDeadGovernment-&gt;fallen civil defense command</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.18>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.19>intention-&gt;intended to be opened only when humanity faced collapse</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.19>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.2>ancientSilos-&gt;ancient military silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.2>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.20>intention-&gt;built to withstand centuries and reopen in humanity’s darkest hour</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.20>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.21>intention-&gt;designed as failsafe supply nodes for rebuilding civilization</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.21>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.22>intention-&gt;meant to be activated only during a planetary extinction event</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.22>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.23>intention-&gt;set to unlock once the collapse protocols were confirmed</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.23>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.24>intention-&gt;intended to serve as last-resort caches for surviving factions</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.24>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.25>containedReward-&gt;vast stockpiles of resources: steel, plasteel, medicine, weaponry, and even preserved cultural relics</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.25>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.26>containedReward-&gt;a wealth of resources: hardened rations, components, medical supplies, and munitions</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.26>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.27>containedReward-&gt;critical survival materials: building materials, medicines, weapons, and schematics</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.27>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.28>containedReward-&gt;tools to rebuild: fuel, tools, seeds, weapons, and encrypted blueprints</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.28>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.29>containedReward-&gt;enough equipment to sustain or restart a new colony</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.29>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.3>ancientSilos-&gt;sealed war-era bunkers</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.3>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.30>containedReward-&gt;a treasure trove of essential gear, preserved through time</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.30>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.31>threat-&gt;Yet the silos are not empty. The corridors within are completely lightless, and something hostile is said to lurk in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.31>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.32>threat-&gt;But time has not left them untouched. The interior is pitch black, and something stirs in the shadows</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.32>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.33>threat-&gt;Explorers report movement inside: faint noises, heavy footsteps, shapes in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.33>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.34>threat-&gt;Survivors speak of hostile entities lurking in the corridors, unseen until it’s too late</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.34>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.35>threat-&gt;Whatever remains inside is not dormant, something guards these forgotten halls</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.35>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.36>threat-&gt;The halls are quiet, but not empty. Something waits inside, cloaked in shadow</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.36>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.37>importantLight-&gt;Activating the power and lighting systems inside is critical</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.37>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.38>importantLight-&gt;Restoring power and activating lights will be vital to survival</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.38>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.39>importantLight-&gt;Without illumination, any movement inside the silo is suicide</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.39>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.4>ancientSilos-&gt;abandoned military silos</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.4>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.40>importantLight-&gt;Light systems must be activated first, or you’ll be helpless in the dark</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.40>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.41>importantLight-&gt;Sight is your only defense. Find a way to power the lights quickly</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.41>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.42>importantLight-&gt;Unless you activate the lights, the silo will be a deathtrap</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.42>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.43>commandMap-&gt;Each silo is also known to contain at least one ancient command desk or map table used to coordinate military movements</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.43>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.44>commandMap-&gt;Most silos house ancient desks or battle maps once used by field commanders</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.44>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.45>commandMap-&gt;Tactical tables scattered inside may contain encrypted maps to other installations</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.45>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.46>commandMap-&gt;Buried among the supplies are command desks filled with strategic data</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.46>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.47>commandMap-&gt;Decoding the maps on-site could reveal new locations tied to Operation: Deadlife</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.47>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.48>commandMap-&gt;Intact terminals and war tables could lead us to the central command</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.48>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.49>questObjective-&gt;The quest will complete once you loot at least a quarter of resources from the silo</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.49>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.5>ancientSilos-&gt;pre-collapse resource vaults</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.5>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.50>questObjective-&gt;Loot at least 25% of the total resources stored in the silo to complete the quest</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.50>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.51>questObjective-&gt;The mission ends once a significant portion of the stored goods have been secured</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.51>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.52>questObjective-&gt;Successfully extracting a quarter of the silo’s contents will fulfill the objective</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.52>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.53>questObjective-&gt;You’ll need to claim at least a fourth of the silo’s supplies to mark this operation complete</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.53>
  <VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.54>questObjective-&gt;Once enough materials have been secured and hauled out, the quest will be marked complete</VQE_Deadlife_AncientSilo.questDescriptionRules.rulesStrings.54>
